74
00:33:06,050 --> 00:33:31,261
just because of where we're at as a society right now. So what does the current state of racial reckoning and a growing retreat from healthy dialogue about diversity, equity, and inclusion mean for establishing greater community? I know it's a long question, but if you kind of distill it. Yeah, yeah.

75
00:33:33,708 --> 00:34:00,573
I think that we're not at a new place. We're definitely not at a new place. And I think we suffer for lack of remembering the history. And I know that we've done a lot of, sometimes it's easier to just bite your tongue, hold, you're right.

76
00:34:01,417 --> 00:34:13,735
Yeah, this generation, sort of the gen alpha, I keep telling them, this is an emotional group. This is an emotional group. And so I think that, you know,

77
00:34:14,933 --> 00:34:40,381
Grace is a big thing that I've learned, right? Yes. And that, yeah, it just, it goes beyond how we feel. I think it goes beyond how we feel, and I think it's time for a lot of folks, I often say, you know, you need to take off your lenses, and I need you to put in my lenses from the center, from our point of view. Put these lenses on, okay, and now let's have our conversation from this point of view.

78
00:34:40,381 --> 00:34:50,590
Because a lot of times I can speak directly as sort of the executive director of the historic black organization.

79
00:34:50,978 --> 00:35:15,768
hear that there's times when I feel the voice shrinking and being snuffed out. There's times where we've got to carry a big stick. And I think we're at a point where we've done a lot of cow tailing to move the process forward, to get things done.

80
00:35:15,768 --> 00:35:25,505
But we've taken that sort of as far as we can go. And I think it's time, look, we really need to put up the mirror. We need to have these conversations. Let's have the conversations so then.

81
00:35:25,623 --> 00:35:49,467
we can deal with the emotionality of it, and then let's walk it forward, right? Because we're doing a lot of time spinning in emotion, we're not solving anything. And sometimes when you're in a highly intellectual community that we love to talk about problems, we love to talk about how we got here, and the sociology of it, and why it's

82
00:35:49,906 --> 00:36:05,617
But then we never solve anything, right? We get caught up in the accolades of, well, we've discussed that. The problem is we've got to get to solving that because we're just passing it down, passing it down, passing it down. And I think

83
00:36:06,545 --> 00:36:28,195
